<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6277] Metrics for scan object are overwritten when restart() is called</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6277</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4145&quot; title=&quot;Provide metrics for hbase client&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4145&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4145&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;br/&gt;
There&apos;s an issue in &lt;tt&gt;TableRecordReaderImpl&lt;/tt&gt;. Calling restart() does this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void restart(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] firstRow) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
  currentScan = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Scan(scan);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which by itself is fine since the metrics will be copied from &lt;b&gt;scan&lt;/b&gt; to &lt;b&gt;currentScan&lt;/b&gt;, except that it&apos;s &lt;b&gt;currentScan&lt;/b&gt; that has the updated metrics not &lt;b&gt;scan&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In other words, &lt;b&gt;currentScan&lt;/b&gt; is the object that is used for scanning so it contains the metrics. If restart() is called, that object is overwritten by the original definition of the &lt;tt&gt;Scan&lt;/tt&gt;. I think to fix this we could grab the metrics from &lt;b&gt;currentScan&lt;/b&gt; first then set them back on the new object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
